Using the ngResource Module
---------------------------

- The ngResouces module enables interaction with RESTful Web services by using the $resource service 
- $resource is a higher level abstraction over the $http service
- $http handles general purpose communication with the HTTP server whereas...
- $resource is used specifically for interacting with RESTful APIs

- To use $resource, you need to include the ngResource module:
	
	<script src="angular-resource.js">
	<script src="ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/X.Y.Z/angular-resource.js">

	- Download it or use its CDN

Demo:

